  1x <a href="javascript:card_browser(90)">Relics of Moria</a><br>
  1x <a href="javascript:card_browser(81)">Guard Commander</a><br>
  1x trolls keyward<br>
  1x foul things<br>
  1x <a href="javascript:card_browser(80)">Goblin Warrior</a><br>
  1x goblin scrabbler<br>
  2x ulaire nertea, MODG    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Strategy</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> How to play<br>
<br>
Bid 4 (unless you know your opponent plays Nazgul, then go for 3.)Go get Aragorn. Depending on your opening hand and what minions your opponent is playing, you choose to stop at site two or to move ahead to rivendell. Just one example. Opponents site two is the weatherhills, if there is still a nazgul (and perhaps black breath) on table, you will choose to stop,unless you drew thrors map,aragorns bow/Arv etc.<br>
Almost any time your opponent will move slowly trough Moria. Take advantage by moving there twice somewhere (unless you did not drew the right cards.) Otherwise you will or have to kill your opponent or pass him at the shores if he does not play orcs. At this time you will have played 90% of your most important fellowship cards.( still 10 cards in the deck). If your opponent will definitele go first to site 9, go easy on the cards( no reconcile, save a they are coming in your hand.)Only one remark about site 7: it skips archery. Some people say then why does your fellowship play archery. Now if i am ahead, my opponent plays his site. Depending on what i can do there, i will move from 6 to 8, leaving him no choice to play on his shadow side. Now if my opponent is ahead, I want to skip archery for sure to stop him at site 7. With a good hand, I will stop him at site 8, and then depending on my hand, I will move from 7 to 9.<br>
<br>
Anti-cards<br>
<br>
Most cards in the decks are of course replacable. I, personally look at all these decks to see the different ways people counter strategies, not to copy decks.<br>
If a minion base is heavily played in your area, just double the flaming brand, the bow, the arv, the elbereth or the mithril coat. Feel free to add other cards. While the free peoples anti-cards are concrete, minion base is more abstract.<br>
My opponents mostly sacrifice hobbits to the troll or balrog, so i replaced the whip and the hammer with the spear. they also play big companies with one or two big guys with an armor, so that makes the whip and the hammer less useful. If your opponents don&#39;t counter <br>
Moria so hard like mine, feel free to put this cards in. Against unprepared opponents, these cards come very hard. I also play instead of enquea nertea because that card is more to the theme of swarming and is also better against very large fellowships (7+) which I often see.<br>
Then there are the cards that remove conditions if you think they are not enough as a threat, you should not play them. My experience is that the scrabbler is very useful and that the rare tume you meet a dwarf deck, the warrior kicks butt. </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP" COLSPAN="2"><font class="bfont"> <a href="/lotr/decks/decks.php">Back to Decks Directory</a> | <A HREF="/lotr/decks/decks.php?reviews=23315"> Read Reviews </A> | <a href="deckprint.php?deck=23315" TARGET="BLANK_"> Printer Friendly</a></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE><a name="review"></a><font class="h2font">In order to review decks you must be a registered member. <A href="/lotr/main/join.php">Sign up for free!</A></font></font></td><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_09.gif"></td></tr>
